(1) A natural person commits an administrative offense by:

- a) operating the land part of a port without a permit from the navigation authority, in contravention of § 6 (3);

- b) carrying out an activity prohibited under § 8 (5) in a public port;

- c) operating a landing stage, transshipment point, mooring point or anchorage without a permit from the navigation authority, in contravention of § 8a (1);

- d) violating the conditions stipulated in the permit for operating a landing stage, transshipment point, mooring point or anchorage under § 8a (5);

- e) as an operator of a landing stage, transshipment point, mooring point or anchorage,

- 1. failing to mark the landing stage, transshipment point, mooring point or anchorage with navigation marks, in contravention of § 8a (7) (a), or

- 2. failing to provide information on the manner and extent of use of the landing stage, transshipment point, mooring point or anchorage upon request by the navigation authority, in contravention of § 8a (7) (b);

- f) as the owner of a vessel, failing to notify the navigation authority that the vessel has become waste, in contravention of § 10d (5);

- g) as the owner of a vessel, failing to notify the navigation authority of changes to data recorded in the navigation register or the small vessels register, in contravention of § 14 (5) or § 15a (4);

- h) damaging navigation marks or other navigation equipment located on or near a waterway, using them for mooring a vessel, or placing an object on or near a waterway that is interchangeable with navigation marks, in contravention of § 29a (1);

- i) placing, removing or relocating navigation marks without the consent of the navigation authority, in contravention of § 29a (2);

- j) violating the prohibition of sailing on a surfboard with a sail or using a traction kite, in contravention of § 29e (2);

- k) violating the prohibition of water skiing or similar activity operated by towing behind a vessel, in contravention of § 29f (2);

- l) operating activities listed in § 30a (1) outside the parts of the waterway designated for their operation;

- m) violating any of the prohibitions on a designated water area under § 30a (7), or

- n) transporting dangerous goods on an inland waterway in contravention of § 36 (2).

(2) A natural person commits an administrative offense by:

- a) performing the function of a crew member of a vessel without holding a valid document proving the authorization necessary for its performance;

- b) performing the function of a vessel master who navigates using radar or ensures the movement of a pushed convoy of vessels with an area of at least 7,000 m^2, without holding a valid document proving the special authorization necessary for its performance;

- c) performing the function of a master of a vessel listed in § 24a (1) that uses liquefied natural gas as fuel, without holding a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert;

- d) performing the activity of a passenger transport expert or a liquefied natural gas expert without holding a valid document proving the authorization necessary for its performance;

- e) operating a floating machine without holding a valid machine operator's certificate or gaining experience in operating a floating machine under the supervision of a holder of a valid machine operator's competence certificate;

- f) as a vessel master, failing to record data in the crew member's service record book according to § 24f (2);

- g) as a holder of a crew member qualification certificate, a crew member competence certificate, a passenger transport expert qualification certificate, a liquefied natural gas expert qualification certificate or a machine operator's competence certificate, in contravention of this Act,

- 1. violating the prohibition of activity consisting of performing the function of a crew member of a vessel, navigating a vessel using radar or a vessel that ensures the movement of a pushed convoy of vessels with an area of at least 7,000 m^2, performing the activity of a passenger transport expert or a liquefied natural gas expert, or operating a floating machine,

- 2. failing to submit or hand over this document to the navigation authority, or

- 3. failing to report the loss, destruction, theft or damage of this document or service record book, or a change of their first name(s) or surname, or failing to hand over the service record book to the navigation authority;

- h) as a crew member of a vessel listed in § 24a (1), failing to carry a valid document proving authorization to perform the relevant crew member function during its operation, in contravention of § 24z (1);

- i) as a vessel master,

- 1. who navigates using radar or ensures the movement of a pushed convoy of vessels with an area of at least 7,000 m^2, failing to carry a valid document proving special authorization to perform the function of master of such a vessel during its operation, in contravention of § 24z (1) (a),

- 2. who is listed in § 24a (1) and uses liquefied natural gas as fuel, failing to carry a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert during its operation, in contravention of § 24z (1) (b), or

- 3. who is a holder of a vessel master qualification certificate, failing to carry a service record book during the operation of the vessel, in contravention of § 24z (1) (c);

- j) as a person performing the activities of a passenger transport expert or a liquefied natural gas expert, failing to carry a valid document proving authorization for its performance, in contravention of § 24z (2) or (3);

- k) as a machine operator, failing to carry a valid machine operator's competence certificate during the operation of a floating machine, in contravention of § 24z (4);

- l) in contravention of this Act, navigating a small vessel subject to registration under this Act, which is not a vessel under § 24a (1), or a recreational vessel, which is not a small vessel, without holding a valid document proving authorization to navigate it;

- m) as a holder of a small vessel master's competence certificate or an international recreational vessel master's competence certificate, in contravention of this Act,

- 1. violating the prohibition of activity consisting of navigating a small or recreational vessel,

- 2. failing to submit or hand over this certificate to the navigation authority, or

- 3. failing to report the loss, destruction, theft or damage of the certificate or a change of their first name(s) or surname to the navigation authority;

- n) as a master of a small or recreational vessel, failing to carry a valid small vessel master's competence certificate or recreational vessel master's competence certificate during its operation, in contravention of § 26k;

- o) as a machine operator,

- 1. not being present on board the floating machine during its operation, in contravention of § 29b (6) (a), or

- 2. failing to fulfill any of the obligations listed in § 29b (6) (b);

- p) performing

- 1. the function of a crew member of a vessel, the activity of a passenger transport expert or the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert, operating a floating machine, or navigating a small or recreational vessel under the influence of alcohol or other addictive substance; this does not apply if the ability to navigate the vessel is affected by the consumption of alcohol by the master of a small vessel without its own engine propulsion not subject to registration under this Act, where the detected alcohol content is less than 0.5 per mille, and this vessel is navigated on an unmonitored waterway, a dedicated waterway, on the Bečva watercourse from Přerov to the mouth of the Morava watercourse, or on the Morava watercourse from the mouth of the Bečva watercourse to river km 196.0 (Strž weir), or

- 2. another activity related to navigation other than the activity listed in point 1, during which they could endanger the life or health of another person or damage property, under the influence of alcohol or other addictive substance; this does not apply if the ability to perform this activity is affected by the consumption of alcohol and this activity is performed on a small vessel without its own engine propulsion not subject to registration under this Act, which is navigated on an unmonitored waterway, a dedicated waterway, on the Bečva watercourse from Přerov to the mouth of the Morava watercourse, or on the Morava watercourse from the mouth of the Bečva watercourse to river km 196.0 (Strž weir), or

- q) as a crew member of a vessel, a person performing the activity of a passenger transport expert or a liquefied natural gas expert, a machine operator or a master of a small or recreational vessel, failing to undergo an indicative examination or a specialized medical examination upon request by the navigation authority, in contravention of § 29b (7).

(3) A natural person, as a participant in navigation traffic on a waterway, commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to follow instructions to ensure the safety and smooth flow of navigation traffic under § 22b (1);

- b) endangering the safety or smooth flow of navigation traffic, human life or health, causing property damage, a navigation accident or an obstruction on the waterway, or polluting the watercourse or otherwise damaging the environment, in contravention of § 29 (1);

- c) failing to follow navigation marks, sound or light signals, in contravention of § 29 (2);

- d) failing to take measures to remove an obstruction on the waterway or failing to visibly mark an obstruction on the waterway, in contravention of § 29 (3);

- e) towing or using fishing gear in contravention of § 29c (1) or (3);

- f) swimming or diving in a place where swimming or diving is prohibited under § 29d (1);

- g) carrying out special transport without a permit from the navigation authority, in contravention of § 29g (1);

- h) organizing an event on a monitored waterway without a permit from the navigation authority or failing to comply with the conditions stipulated in the permit, in contravention of § 29h, or

- i) using special signaling on a vessel without a permit from the navigation authority, in contravention of § 29j (1).

(4) A crew member of a vessel or another person on a vessel commits an administrative offense by failing to follow the master's order issued to ensure the safety and smooth flow of navigation traffic, in contravention of § 29b (5).

(5) The master of a vessel commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to ensure that during the operation of the vessel in port, the safety of persons on the vessel or other participants in navigation traffic is not endangered, or that vessels, structures on the waterway or the environment are not endangered or damaged, in contravention of § 8 (1) and (6);

- b) failing to report the entry of a vessel into a public port or the departure of a vessel from a public port, in contravention of § 8 (4) and (6);

- c) failing to record mandatory data in the vessel documents in the prescribed manner, in contravention of § 18 (2);

- d) failing to present vessel documents upon request, in contravention of § 18 (3);

- e) violating the prohibition of navigation under § 22 (1);

- f) violating the prohibition of drifting under § 22 (3);

- g) disregarding restrictions, stoppages or other adjustments to navigation traffic issued by a general measure under § 22a (1);

- h) failing to fulfill any of the obligations stipulated in § 29b (1) to (3) in the interest of ensuring the safety of navigation traffic;

- i) failing to ensure that the state flag of the Czech Republic is flown on the vessel, in contravention of § 29b (4);

- j) failing to ensure the reporting of an accident involving the vessel they are navigating, in contravention of § 31 (2);

- k) departing with the vessel from the scene of an accident or failing to transport the vessel after an accident to the nearest shallow or other safe place, in contravention of § 31 (3), or

- l) in contravention of § 32e (2),

- 1. failing to use during navigation equipment or software intended for monitoring the position and movement of vessels or displaying electronic navigation charts and information on the position and movement of vessels, or

- 2. failing to report a malfunction of this equipment or software to the administrator of the river information services system.

(6) The master of a vessel that is part of a vessel convoy commits an administrative offense by failing to follow the orders of the convoy master, in contravention of § 29b (5).

(7) The master of a vessel commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to ensure the safety of persons participating in sailing on a surfboard with a sail or using a traction kite, or the safety of other participants in navigation traffic, in contravention of § 29e (1), or

- b) failing to ensure the safety of a water skier or a person performing a similar activity towed behind a vessel, or the safety of other participants in navigation traffic, in contravention of § 29f (1).

(8) A natural person, as a vessel operator, commits an administrative offense by:

- a) operating a vessel on a waterway that cannot be operated on the waterway under § 9 (1) to (3) or § 10c (1);

- b) failing to ensure that the vessel is equipped with identification marks, load lines or draft scales or equipped with the prescribed vessel documents, in contravention of § 18 (1);

- c) failing to ensure that a single logbook is kept for the vessel, in contravention of § 18 (2);

- d) failing to present vessel documents upon request, in contravention of § 18 (3);

- e) operating a vessel on a waterway without agreed liability insurance for damage from vessel operation, in contravention of § 19 (1);

- f) failing to equip the vessel with optical or sound signaling, rescue equipment or equipment necessary for waste disposal, radiotelephone or other equipment serving to ensure navigation safety, in contravention of § 23a (1);

- g) failing to equip the vessel so that the state flag of the Czech Republic can be flown on it, in contravention of § 23a (2);

- h) failing to ensure the manning of the vessel by a crew in the required number and professional composition, in contravention of § 24 (2);

- i) failing to ensure that the activity of a passenger transport expert is performed by a person who holds a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a passenger transport expert, in contravention of § 24n (8);

- j) failing to ensure that the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert is performed by a person who holds a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert, in contravention of § 24n (8);

- k) failing to ensure that the operation of a floating machine is performed by a person who holds a valid machine operator's certificate or is gaining experience in operating a floating machine under the supervision of a holder of a valid machine operator's competence certificate, in contravention of § 24n (8), or

- l) failing to equip the vessel with equipment or software intended for monitoring the position and movement of vessels or displaying electronic navigation charts and information on the position and movement of vessels, in contravention of § 32e (1).

(9) A natural person, as a vessel operator or owner, commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to hand over an invalid vessel certificate to the navigation authority within the stipulated period, in contravention of § 10b (3);

- b) failing to report the loss, theft, damage or destruction of a vessel certificate to the navigation authority, in contravention of § 11 (1);

- c) failing to ensure a watch or supervision over the vessel, in contravention of § 23a (3), or

- d) failing to place the vessel in a port with a protective function or another protected place before reaching a water level at which navigation is prohibited, or failing to secure the vessel before the winter period, in contravention of § 23a (4).

(10) The master of a vessel or a natural person as a vessel operator commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to ensure the reporting of an accident involving the vessel they operate, in contravention of § 31 (2), or

- b) failing to provide the administrator of the river information services system with information relating to the support of traffic and transport management in inland navigation under § 32b (2) (a).

(11) A natural person, as a person swimming, commits an administrative offense by endangering the safety or smooth flow of navigation, in contravention of § 29d (4).

(12) A natural person, as a person diving, commits an administrative offense by failing to mark the dive site on the surface with a visible safety mark, in contravention of § 29d (6).

(13) A natural person, as a gravel pit operator, commits an administrative offense by failing to fulfill any of the obligations stipulated in § 29i (1).

(14) A natural person, as a floating facility operator, commits an administrative offense by failing to ensure the presence of a person ensuring the operation of the floating facility under § 23a (5).

(15) A fine may be imposed for an administrative offense:

- a) up to CZK 1,000,000, in the case of an administrative offense under paragraph 1 (n) or paragraph 8 (e);

- b) up to CZK 500,000, in the case of an administrative offense under paragraph 1 (a) or (c), paragraph 8 (a), (f), (h), (i), (j) or (k) or paragraph 9 (d);

- c) up to CZK 100,000, in the case of an administrative offense under paragraph 1 (d), paragraph 1 (e) point 1, paragraph 1 (h), (i), (j), (k), (l) or (m), paragraph 2 (a), (b), (c), (d), (e), (f), paragraph 2 (g) point 1 or paragraph 2 (o), paragraph 3 (b), (d), (g) or (h), paragraph 5 (c), (e), (g), (h), (j) or (k), paragraph 6, paragraph 8 (b), (c) or (l) or paragraph 10 or 14;

- d) up to CZK 50,000, in the case of an administrative offense under paragraph 2 (l), paragraph 2 (m) point 1, paragraph 2 (p) or (q), paragraph 3 (c) or (e), paragraph 4, paragraph 5 (a), (f), (i) or paragraph 5 (l) point 1, paragraph 7, paragraph 9 (c) or paragraph 11 or 12;

- e) up to CZK 10,000, in the case of an administrative offense under paragraph 1 (b), paragraph 1 (e) point 2, paragraph 1 (f) or (g), paragraph 2 (g) point 2 or 3, paragraph 2 (h), (i), (j), (k), paragraph 2 (m) point 2 or 3 or paragraph 2 (n), paragraph 3 (a), (f) or (i), paragraph 5 (b), (d) or paragraph 5 (l) point 2, paragraph 8 (d) or (g), paragraph 9 (a) or (b) or paragraph 13.

(16) A prohibition of activity for up to 2 years may be imposed for an administrative offense under paragraph 2 (a), (b), (c), (d), (e), (l), (p) or (q).

(17) On-the-spot fine may be imposed by:

- a) the navigation authority only for administrative offenses under paragraph 1 (b), (d), paragraph 1 (e) point 1, paragraph 1 (g), (h), (j), (k), (l) or (m), paragraph 2 (h), (i), (j), (k) or (n), paragraph 3 (c), (d), (e), (f) or (i), paragraph 4, paragraph 5 (a), (b), (c), (d), (e), (f), (g), (h), (i), (j) or (k), paragraph 7, paragraph 8 (a), (b), (d), (f) or (g), paragraph 9 (c), paragraph 10 (a) or (b) or paragraph 11, 12, 13 or 14;

- b) the Police of the Czech Republic only for administrative offenses under paragraph 1 (b), if it concerns a violation of the prohibition under § 8 (5) (a), paragraph 1 (h), (j), (k), (l) or (m), paragraph 2 (h), (i), (j), (k) or (n), paragraph 3 (c), (d), (e), (f) or (i), paragraph 5 (a), (d), (e), (g), (h) or (i) or paragraph 7 or 11.

p44.text:
(1) A legal entity or a self-employed natural person commits an administrative offense by:

- a) operating the land part of a port without a permit from the navigation authority, in violation of § 6 (3);

- b) operating a landing stage, transhipment point, mooring point or anchorage without a permit from the navigation authority, in violation of § 8a (1);

- c) violating the conditions stipulated in the permit for operating a landing stage, transhipment point, mooring point or anchorage pursuant to § 8a (5);

- d) as the operator of a landing stage, transhipment point, mooring point or anchorage,

- 1. failing to mark the landing stage, transhipment point, mooring point or anchorage with navigation signs, in violation of § 8a (7) (a), or

- 2. failing to provide information on the manner and extent of use of the landing stage, transhipment point, mooring point or anchorage upon request by the navigation authority, in violation of § 8a (7) (b);

- e) as the owner of a vessel, failing to notify the navigation authority that the vessel has become waste, in violation of § 10d (5);

- f) as the owner of a vessel, failing to notify the navigation authority of changes to data recorded in the navigation register or the small vessel register, in violation of § 14 (5) or § 15a (4);

- g) damaging navigation signs or other navigation equipment located on or near a waterway, using them for mooring a vessel, or placing an object on or near a waterway that is interchangeable with navigation signs, in violation of § 29a (1);

- h) placing, removing or relocating navigation signs, in violation of § 29a (2);

- i) operating a small vessel rental service without a permit from the navigation authority, in violation of § 30b (1), or

- j) as the operator of a small vessel rental service,

- 1. failing to comply with the conditions stipulated in the permit or renting a vessel other than that specified in the permit without the consent of the navigation authority, in violation of § 30b (4), or

- 2. failing to inform the navigation authority of a change in the facts stated in the application or in the documents attached thereto, in violation of § 30b (5).

(2) The waterway administrator commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to administer the waterway in such a way as to ensure safe navigation, failing to mark the monitored waterway with navigation signs, or failing to maintain such signs, in violation of § 5 (5);

- b) failing to cooperate with the operator of the land part of the port in ensuring safe port operation, in violation of § 7 (3);

- c) failing to notify the navigation authority of the placement, removal or relocation of navigation signs, in violation of § 29a (2), or

- d) failing to mark the defined water area with navigation signs, in violation of § 30a (8).

(3) The administrator of a commercially used waterway commits an administrative offense by failing to equip vessels or navigation objects with radio stations, in violation of § 23 (4).

(4) The operator of the land part of a port commits an administrative offense by:

- a) operating the land part of a port without a permit from the navigation authority, in violation of § 6 (3);

- b) violating the conditions stipulated in the permit for operating the land part of a port pursuant to § 6 (6);

- c) failing to publish a price list containing prices for the use of the land part of the port, in violation of § 6b (3);

- d) failing to operate the land part of the port for the entire period of validity of the permit or failing to maintain it in a condition that allows safe navigation in the port, in violation of § 7 (1) (a);

- e) failing to publish rules or data pursuant to § 7 (1) (b);

- f) failing to mark places for handling flammable or dangerous goods, for storing solid and liquid waste from vessels, or for taking water and electricity, in violation of § 7 (1) (c);

- g) failing to keep records of loaded and unloaded vessels or the type and quantity of transhipped cargo, in violation of § 7 (1) (d);

- h) failing to mark places designated for vessel mooring with navigation signs, in violation of § 7 (1) (e), or

- i) failing to cooperate with the waterway administrator in ensuring safe port operation, in violation of § 7 (3).

(5) The operator of the land part of a public port commits an administrative offense by failing to equip vessels or port facilities with radio stations, in violation of § 23 (4).

(6) A legal entity or a self-employed natural person, as the operator of a vessel, commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to use permanent berths designated by the operator of the land part of a public port for long-term mooring of a vessel, in violation of § 8 (2);

- b) operating a vessel on a waterway that cannot be operated on the waterway pursuant to § 9 (1) to (3) or § 10c (1);

- c) failing to ensure that the vessel is provided with identification marks, load lines or draught scales or equipped with prescribed ship's documents, in violation of § 18 (1);

- d) failing to ensure that only one ship's logbook is kept for the vessel, in violation of § 18 (2);

- e) failing to present ship's documents upon request, in violation of § 18 (3);

- f) operating a vessel on a waterway without agreed liability insurance for damage from vessel operation, in violation of § 19 (1);

- g) failing to adapt the operation of the vessel on the waterway to the nature and condition of the waterway, in violation of § 23 (1);

- h) failing to equip the vessel with optical or acoustic signaling, rescue equipment or means necessary for waste disposal, radiotelephone or other equipment serving to ensure navigation safety, in violation of § 23a (1);

- i) failing to ensure that the state flag of the Czech Republic is flown on the vessel, in violation of § 23a (2);

- j) failing to ensure that the vessel is operated by a crew of the required number and professional composition, in violation of § 24 (2);

- k) failing to ensure that the activity of a “passenger transport expert” is performed by a person who holds a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a passenger transport expert, in violation of § 24n (8);

- l) failing to ensure that the activity of a “liquefied natural gas expert” is performed by a person who holds a valid document proving authorization to perform the activity of a liquefied natural gas expert, in violation of § 24n (8);

- m) failing to ensure that the operation of a floating machine is performed by a person who holds a valid master mechanic's certificate or is gaining experience in operating a floating machine under the supervision of a holder of a valid master mechanic's certificate of competency, in violation of § 24n (8);

- n) failing to ensure that an accident of a vessel operated by it is reported, in violation of § 31 (2);

- o) failing to equip the vessel with equipment or software intended for tracking the position and movement of vessels or displaying electronic navigation maps and information on the position and movement of vessels, in violation of § 32e (1), or

- p) transporting dangerous goods on an inland waterway in violation of § 36 (2).

(7) A legal entity or a self-employed natural person, as the operator or owner of a vessel, commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to hand over an invalid vessel certificate to the navigation authority within the stipulated period, in violation of § 10b (3);

- b) failing to report the loss, theft, damage or destruction of a vessel certificate to the navigation authority, in violation of § 11 (1);

- c) failing to ensure a watch or supervision over the vessel, in violation of § 23a (3), or

- d) failing to place the vessel in a port with a protective function or in another protected place before reaching a water level at which navigation is prohibited, or failing to secure the vessel before the winter period, in violation of § 23a (4).

(8) The operator of water transport commits an administrative offense by:

- a) failing to equip the vessel with radio stations, in violation of § 23 (4), or

- b) failing to notify the navigation authority without undue delay of a change in the circumstances on the basis of which a certificate was issued pursuant to directly applicable European Union regulation^7a), in violation of § 35a (2) or in violation of directly applicable European Union regulation^21).

(9) The operator of public water transport commits an administrative offense by failing to publish the contractual transport conditions under which public transport will be operated, the timetable, the tariff, the start date of operation, or the extent of barrier-free access, in violation of § 35 (2).

(10) The carrier commits an administrative offense by, in violation of the directly applicable European Union regulation on the rights of passengers when travelling by sea and inland waterways^20):

- a) failing to issue a transport document to the passenger;

- b) failing to provide free assistance to a person with reduced mobility in the port, during embarkation and disembarkation, or on board the ship;

- c) failing to ensure training focused on issues of persons with disabilities;

- d) failing to provide assistance, reimbursement of fare, or re-routing in the event of cancellation or delay of arrival or departure, or

- e) failing to provide passengers with adequate information on the course of transport, on passenger rights, or failing to have an accessible mechanism for handling complaints concerning passenger rights.

(11) The carrier or seller of transport documents commits an administrative offense by discriminating in the application of contractual conditions and tariffs, in violation of the directly applicable European Union regulation on the rights of passengers when travelling by sea and inland waterways^20).

(12) The carrier, travel agency operator or tour operator commits an administrative offense by refusing to accept a reservation, issue a transport document or embark persons due to disability or reduced mobility, in violation of the directly applicable European Union regulation on the rights of passengers when travelling by sea and inland waterways^20).

(13) The carrier, operator of the land part of a port or tour operator commits an administrative offense by failing to publish the access conditions applicable to the transport of persons with reduced mobility and accompanying persons, in violation of the directly applicable European Union regulation on the rights of passengers when travelling by sea and inland waterways^20).

(14) A legal entity or a self-employed natural person as the operator of a vessel, waterway administrator or port operator commits an administrative offense by failing to ensure the provision of information relating to the support of traffic and transport management in inland navigation to the administrator of the river information services system, in violation of § 32b (2).

(15) A legal entity or a self-employed natural person as the operator of a floating facility commits an administrative offense by failing to ensure the presence of a person ensuring the operation of the floating facility pursuant to § 23a (5).

(16) A fine may be imposed for an administrative offense:

- a) up to CZK 1,000,000, if it is an administrative offense pursuant to paragraph 6 (f) or (p);

- b) up to CZK 500,000, if it is an administrative offense pursuant to paragraph 1 (a), paragraph 3, paragraph 4 (a), (b), (d) or (e), paragraph 5, paragraph 6 (b), (h), (j), (k), (l) or (m), paragraph 7 (d) or paragraph 8;

- c) up to CZK 200,000, if it is an administrative offense pursuant to paragraph 1 (b), (c) or (i), paragraph 2, paragraph 4 (c), (f) or (i), paragraph 6 (g) or (o), paragraph 9, paragraph 10 (b) or paragraph 11, 12 or 13;

- d) up to CZK 100,000, if it is an administrative offense pursuant to paragraph 1 (d) point 1, (g), (h) or (j) point 1, paragraph 4 (g) or (h), paragraph 6 (a), (c), (d) or (n), paragraph 7 (c), paragraph 10 (c), (d) or (e) or paragraph 14 or 15;

- e) up to CZK 10,000, if it is an administrative offense pursuant to paragraph 1 (d) point 2, (e), (f) or (j) point 2, paragraph 6 (e) or (i), paragraph 7 (a) or (b) or paragraph 10 (a).
